bubble chamber

00:00:09.680 --> 00:00:11.860
it bends the path of the electron

00:00:11.860 --> 00:00:13.540
because the electron is negatively charged.

00:00:13.540 --> 00:00:16.020
Things don't change direction of their own
accord.

00:00:16.020 --> 00:00:19.640
Things like to go in a straight line unless
you influence them.

00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:23.440
If you make a magnetic field, negatively charged
particles will go one way,

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:24.740
and positives the other.

00:00:25.140 --> 00:00:27.820
Neutral particles don't leave any trail at
all in these pictures.

00:00:27.820 --> 00:00:29.380
Now let's look at the next picture.

00:00:29.380 --> 00:00:31.320
If you really turn on the magnetic field,

00:00:31.320 --> 00:00:34.620
your electron will spiral round and round
and round and round.

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:37.860
As it slows down the spiral gets tighter and
tighter and tighter.

00:00:38.180 --> 00:00:41.940
It looks like the picture of a snail from
the top or something like that.

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:43.760
Now let's look at the next one.

00:00:44.660 --> 00:00:47.900
Now this has got a lot of information. It's
a beautiful picture.

00:00:48.320 --> 00:00:51.520
At this point here an electron's been knocked
out of the atom

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:54.540
and shoots off very high speed curving very
slightly.

00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:59.940
I know it's high speed because when you go
fast you only curve a little bit.

00:00:59.940 --> 00:01:04.040
If you go slow, you'll curve all the way around
when you get given the sideways kick.

00:01:04.820 --> 00:01:08.040
But look at this. Here's an electron that
started off slow.

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:10.260
It's really gone into a very tight spiral.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:15.740
But on the other side there's the same thing
going the other way.

00:01:16.640 --> 00:01:20.900
Negatively charged particles go one way, positives
go the other.

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:25.800
This, the red trail at the bottom, is a positively
charged electron.

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:30.880
The exact mirror image of the regular negative
electron.

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:33.140
It's an example of antimatter.

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:35.180
Captured here on film.

00:01:35.980 --> 00:01:39.760
This is antimatter, it's as real as the electrons
are real.

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:46.660
Now over here, an electron and its antimatter
partner,

00:01:46.680 --> 00:01:49.160
which is called a positron by the way, is
produced.

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.920
But between here and here, nothing appears
to have happened.

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:53.840
These appear to have appeared out of nowhere.

00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:56.060
Well that doesn't make sense at all.

00:01:56.069 --> 00:01:59.399
What's happened is that something without
any charge at all

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:02.780
has gone from here to here and left no trail.

00:02:03.240 --> 00:02:06.900
But we recognise he was there the moment it
did this.

